<br>
The main two and stick out in my mind was POM.  Over and over being told this zone was working as intended when people were wondering what to do with the card drops.  Well, there was SUPPOSED to be a vendor in RV selling a kit that you could combine those cards to make items.  The vendor, nor the kit, was in RV for two months and Verant idly sat and watched while people chased their own shadow. <br>
<br>
The next was saying this 30 foot human was a result of the screenshot taker not patching Velious.  Which, after every patch they do to upgrade models, they announce model upgrades and when to patch Kunark or Velious. The model was not in place, and the script was not working as intended - they were busted on this and still say &quot;Sleepers is working as intended&quot;.  Just as they did with POM when people were wasting their time on card quests which would obviously never be completed.  <br>
<br>
The point is, the longer you waste your time the more revenue comes in.  So in all actuality you spend three months of doing nothing, and you will have gotten no where with what you are trying to achieve and Verant still gets you money. <br>
<br>
We are hearing two sides to the story, and I am quite surprised Verant said something in the first place - which leads me to believe something is up.  Usually they keep very tight lipped about the accounts and situations of others.  We will not know what really happened and we do not know who is telling the truth.  But I know Verant has lied blatently in the past, or their &quot;Working as intended&quot; comments on Sleepers and POM were because they were so ignorant in the testing stages. <br>
<br>
Sometimes it seems like this whole game is a beta test.  And you have to wonder how these foul ups are not taken care of when they release the game in the first place.  If things were tested normally, it doesn't matter how many servers it goes on.  Things that are going wrong are in the data set that is supposedly tested when the expansions or games come out.  Putting them across 20+ servers does not change that data set - meaning they didn't test the zones properly before release.  <br>
<br>
Another good example of this was Kaesora with the human Librarian.  Sometimes still shows up as a human if you can believe that - and yes I patched my Kunark thank you very much. <br>
<br>
Tower of Frozen shadow - the angry relative spawn never functioned and you couldn't get passed the 5th floor for weeks - meanwhile when I petitioned. &quot;Working as intended you just have to figure out how to get that key&quot;. I wasted 3 weeks thinking there was a quest within the tower or outside of the tower with the no drop Signet ring that sometimes drops off of the priest, bride or groom.  Than they fixed it. <br>
<br>
Did they even test the zone?  Obviously not for reasons listed above. <br>
<br>
So my beef with Verant?  If they put as much time into fixing pathing problems, mobs poofing, loot table issues; as into fixing exploits where players can take short cuts - thisgame would be a much better place to be.<br>
<br>
To this date, the golems in frozen shadow on 5,  poof back to the priest and get completely healed when fighting them than come running after you.  And I mean, poof and appear right next to the priest.  Will they ever fix it?  Been 6 months so doubt it. <br>
<br>
To this date the pathing in Chardok has a couple misc. poppers that just appear and disapear, and if you are on the aggro list, the mob will poof to the zone in, summon you from your group if you are in Zone out, and beat the living snot out of you.  How long has this been in the game? <br>
<br>
Do they care?  No.  Because it should have been fixed now and I know at one point that was a serious Customer service issue. <br>
<br>
Meanwhile, you FD split a couple mobs, and at one point that was called an exploit.  You COH to clear aggro and that is exploiting the hate list.  Any tactics or strategies that Verant never thinks of, is turned into an exploit while the bugs that remain in this game harming the players causing them to put more time in, remain. <br>
<br>
